# Feature-slice rules

## Folder layout per feature

```
lib/features/<feature>/
  data/
    dto/                  ← *_dto.dart — Firestore/HTTP boundary types, mappers
    repository/           ← *_repository.dart — Either<Failure, T> writes, Stream<T> reads
    local_db/             ← Hive box managers, offline queues
  domain/
    models/               ← Freezed entities + UI state sealed unions
    <feature>_key.dart    ← Stable identity helpers (e.g. communityStationKey)
  presentation/
    controller/
      <feature>_providers.dart      ← Riverpod providers (repository, controller family)
      <feature>_controller.dart     ← StateNotifier<<Feature>UiState>
    view/                 ← Full-screen widgets
    widget/               ← Feature-private atoms
```

## Boundary rules
- A feature **must not** import `lib/features/<other>/{data,domain}/` internals.
- A feature **may** import:
  - Its own `data/`, `domain/`, `presentation/` siblings.
  - `lib/core/**`.
  - Another feature's **public providers** (the file ending in `_providers.dart`) and **domain models** — sparingly.
- If two features need the same type → move it to `lib/core/domain/`.
- If two features need the same widget → move it to `lib/core/widgets/`.

## Naming
- Providers file ends `_providers.dart`.
- Controller class ends `Controller`.
- UI state class ends `UiState` and is a Freezed sealed union.
- Repository class ends `Repository`.
- DTO ends `Dto`.

## Don't
- ❌ Don't put business logic in widgets — it belongs in the controller.
- ❌ Don't call `FirebaseFirestore.instance` from outside `data/`.
- ❌ Don't expose `DocumentSnapshot` outside `data/` — map to domain in the DTO.
